The paper deals with clustering problems, which are typically studied in computer science under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The additional requirement of a tree-like structure over the obtained clusters suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), which deals with network design, management, and routing. The paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which deals with the analysis of social and information networks. The use of various types of initial elements suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which deals with the development of intelligent algorithms. Finally, the use of greedy-like solving strategies suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning), which deals with the development of algorithms that can learn from data.
